rComments: I took this class as I had an English class requirement, and I am so glad I did. Straightforward grading policy, critique of essays is always fair. Plus he gives lots of opportunities to improve your grade with revision. Would reccommend.

Many opportunities for feedback, which helped upped writing skills not only in his class. He is really sweet and his classes always consisted of discussions. It is difficult to get perfect grades in his class, but only because English is a harsh subject. His feedback is always justified and helps you read your writing through different eyes.

If you listen in lecture about thinking critically about the literature, it is simple to apply that in your papers when you apply effort. He has many astute insights in the literature. Very accessible outside of class and non-condescending about issues of understanding or perception

Professor Orr always comes to class with a positive attitude and great energy. He really enjoys what he teaches and tries to help as much as he can. I do find him to be a tough grader for someone teaching a first-year English course.
